<subSubSection id="C3536509FFD2FFEFFF5B79CCFAD1F8B7" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BF63682FFD2FFEFFF5B79CCFAF8F95F" blockId="19.[151,1437,1483,1906]" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">
<taxonomicName id="4C494D01FFD2FFEFFF5B79CCFF03FA20" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[151,226,1484,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Aethes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEA90FFD2FFEFFF5B79CCFF03FA20" box="[151,226,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">Aethes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(with its many synonyms) is a large genus of about 150 described species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B73FFD2FFEFFBFD79CBFAF0FA20" author="Gilligan, T. M. &amp; Baixeras, J. &amp; Brown, J. W." box="[1073,1297,1483,1510]" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" refId="ref19807" refString="Gilligan, T. M., Baixeras, J. &amp; Brown, J. W. (2019) T @ RTS: Online World Catalogue of the Tortricidae. Version 4.0. Available from: http: // www. tortricid. net / catalogue. asp (accessed 1 April 2019)" type="url" year="2019">
Gilligan 
<emphasis id="B93DEA90FFD2FFEFFB5A79CCFB26FA20" box="[1174,1223,1484,1510]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
), with many additional undescribed species, that is widely distributed in the Palearctic, Nearctic, and Neotropical Regions. Unlike most genera of Cochylina, nearly all North American members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D01FFD2FFEFFC757A14FBE5F9E8" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[953,1028,1556,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Aethes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEA90FFD2FFEFFC757A14FBE5F9E8" box="[953,1028,1556,1582]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">Aethes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be identified to genus by facies alone. The forewing typically has a white to cream ground color with one or more narrow, brown or golden fascia (often interrupted), a small triangular patch near the middle of the hind margin, and/or a brown dash from the base of the forewing; however, there are many exceptions. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B73FFD2FFEFFD3F7A7FFC20F95C" author="Razowski, J." box="[755,961,1663,1690]" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" pagination="387 - 396" refId="ref20891" refString="Razowski, J. (1986 b) List of Neotropical Aethes Billb. and Aethesoides Raz. (Lepidoptera, Tortricidae), with descriptions of new species. Annales Zoologici, 40, 387 - 396." type="journal article" year="1986">Razowski (1986b)</bibRefCitation>
listed the Neotropical species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF63682FFD2FFEFFF0B7AA3FAD1F8B7" blockId="19.[151,1437,1483,1906]" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">
Both the male and female genitalia are fairly diverse morphologically (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B73FFD2FFEFFBD77AA3FAE2F978" author="Sabourin, M. &amp; Miller, W. E. &amp; Metzler, E. H. &amp; Vargo, J. T." box="[1051,1283,1699,1726]" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" pagination="216 - 233" refId="ref21372" refString="Sabourin, M., Miller, W. E., Metzler, E. H. &amp; Vargo, J. T. (2002) Revised identities and new species of Aethes from midwestern North America. Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 56, 216 - 233." type="journal article" year="2002">
Sabourin 
<emphasis id="B93DEA90FFD2FFEFFB4B7AA4FB58F978" box="[1159,1209,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">et al</emphasis>
. 2002
</bibRefCitation>
), as would be expected for a large, widely distributed genus, but males can almost always be assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D01FFD2FFEFFB587AC8FB3EF924" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[1172,1247,1736,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Aethes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEA90FFD2FFEFFB587AC8FB3EF924" box="[1172,1247,1736,1762]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">Aethes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of a pair of slender, hooklike processes from the socii. However, these characteristic processes appear to be lost secondarily in a number of species that based on other characters, including barcodes (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B73FFD2FFEFFBF67B10FAE9F8EC" author="Brown, J. W. &amp; Aarvik, L. &amp; Heikkila, M. &amp; Brown, R. L. &amp; Mutanen, M." box="[1082,1288,1808,1834]" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" refId="ref19624" refString="Brown, J. W., Aarvik, L., Heikkila, M., Brown, R. L. &amp; Mutanen, M. (2019) Molecular phylogeny of Cochylina, with confirmation of its relationship to Euliina (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). Systematic Entomology. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 1238 5" type="book" year="2019">
Brown 
<emphasis id="B93DEA90FFD2FFEFFB417B10FB5FF8EC" box="[1165,1214,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
), fit convincingly in 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D01FFD2FFEFFF3F7B34FEDFF888" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[243,318,1844,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Aethes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEA90FFD2FFEFFF3F7B34FEDFF888" box="[243,318,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">Aethes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Below I transfer one species to 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D01FFD2FFEFFD6B7B34FD13F888" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[679,754,1844,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Aethes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEA90FFD2FFEFFD6B7B34FD13F888" box="[679,754,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">Aethes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and describe a second, the latter the undescribed 
<typeStatus id="54F28820FFD2FFEFFAD97B34FAA4F888" box="[1301,1349,1844,1870]" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD84B73FFD2FFEFFF7A7B58FE81F8B4" author="Pogue, M. G." box="[182,352,1879,1906]" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" refId="ref20442" refString="Pogue, M. G. (1986) A generic revision of the Cochylidae (Lepidoptera) of North America. Ph. D. dissertation, University of Minnesota, Minneapolis, Minnesota, 280 pp." type="book" year="1986">Pogueâ€™s (1986)</bibRefCitation>
manuscript genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C494D01FFD2FFEFFDFF7B58FD98F8B7" authorityName="Pogue and Mickevitch" authorityYear="1990" box="[563,633,1880,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Morta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DEA90FFD2FFEFFDFF7B58FD98F8B7" box="[563,633,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="214">Morta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species lack the sickle-shaped processes from the socii.
</paragraph>
